bondUtilityToken(address,uint256,uint256.details: An operator can only bond to one pod at a time, per network

params.amount: utility token amount to bond (can be greater than minimum)
params.operator: address of operator to bond (can be an ownable smart contract)
params.pod: number of pod to bond to (can be for one that does not exist yet)

constructor.details: Constructor is left empty and init is used instead

crossChainMessage(bytes).details: This function is restricted for use by Holograph Messaging Module only

executeJob(bytes).details: When making this call, if operating criteria is not met, the call will revert

params.bridgeInRequestPayload: the entire cross chain message payload

failedJobExists(bytes32).details: Checks if a failed job exists.

params.jobHash: The hash of the job to check.

getBondedAmount(address).details: Useful for checking how much an operator has bonded

returns.amount: total number of utility token bonded

getBondedPod(address).details: Useful for checking if an operator is currently bonded

returns.pod: number that operator is bonded on, returns zero if not bonded or selected for job

getBondedPodIndex(address).details: Useful for checking if an operator is a fallback for active job

returns.index: currently bonded pod's operator index, returns zero if not in pod or moved out for active job

getBridge().details: Used for beaming holographable assets cross-chain

getHolograph().details: Used for storing a reference to all the primary modules and variables of the protocol

getInterfaces().details: Holograph uses this contract to store data that needs to be accessed by a large portion of the modules

getJobDetails(bytes32).details: The job hash is a keccak256 hash of the entire job payload

returns._0: an OperatorJob struct with details about a specific job

getMessageFee(uint32,uint256,uint256,byt.details: Will provide exact costs on protocol and message side, combine the two to get total@param toChain holograph chain id of destination chain for payload@param gasLimit amount of gas to provide for executing payload on destination chain@param gasPrice maximum amount to pay for gas price, can be set to 0 and will be chose automatically@param crossChainPayload the entire packet being sent cross-chain

returns._0: hlgFee the amount (in wei) of native gas token that will cost for finalizing job on destiantion chain
returns._1: msgFee the amount (in wei) of native gas token that will cost for sending message to destiantion chain
returns._2: dstGasPrice the amount (in wei) that destination message maximum gas price will be

getMessagingModule().details: All cross-chain message requests will get forwarded to this adress

getMinGasPrice().details: The minimum value required to execute a job without it being marked as under priced

getPodBondAmounts(uint256).details: Useful for understanding what is required for bonding to a pod

params.pod: the pod to get bonding amounts for

returns.base: the base bond amount required for a pod
returns.current: the current bond amount required for a pod

getPodOperators(uint256).details: Use paginated getPodOperators function instead if list gets too long

returns.operators: array list of operators in a pod

getPodOperators(uint256,uint256,uint256).details: Use in conjunction with getPodOperatorsLength to know the total length of results

params.index: the array index to start from
params.length: the length of result set to be (will be shorter if reached end of array)

getPodOperatorsLength(uint256).details: Use in conjunction with paginated getPodOperators function

getRegistry().details: This module stores a reference for all deployed holographable smart contracts

getTotalPods().details: This returns number of pods that have been opened via bonding

getUtilityToken().details: This is the official utility token of the Holograph Protocol

init(bytes).details: This function is called by the deployer/factory when creating a contract

params.initPayload: abi encoded payload to use for contract initilaization

jobEstimator(bytes).details: Use this function to estimate the amount of gas that will be used by the bridgeInRequest function      Set a specific gas limit when making this call, subtract return value, to get total gas used      Only use this with a static call

params.bridgeInRequestPayload: abi encoded bytes making up the bridgeInRequest payload

returns._0: the gas amount remaining after the static call is returned

operatorJobExists(bytes32).details: Checks if an operator job exists.

params.jobHash: The hash of the job to check.

recoverJob(bytes).details: If a job fails, it can be manually recovered

params.bridgeInRequestPayload: the entire cross chain message payload

send(uint256,uint256,uint32,address,uint.details: This function is restricted to only be callable by Holograph Bridge

params.bridgeOutPayload: bytes made up of the bridgeOutRequest payload
params.gasLimit: maximum amount of gas to spend for executing the beam on destination chain
params.gasPrice: maximum amount of gas price (in destination chain native gas token) to pay on destination chain
params.holographableContract: address of the contract for which the bridge request is being made
params.nonce: incremented number used to ensure job hashes are unique
params.toChain: Holograph Chain ID where the beam is being sent to

params.bridge: address of the Holograph Bridge smart contract to use

params.holograph: address of the Holograph Protocol smart contract to use

params.interfaces: address of the Holograph Interfaces smart contract to use

params.messagingModule: address of the LayerZero Endpoint to use

params.minGasPrice: amount to set for minimum gas price

params.registry: address of the Holograph Registry smart contract to use

params.utilityToken: address of the Holograph Utility Token smart contract to use

topupUtilityToken(address,uint256).details: Useful function if an operator got slashed and wants to add a safety buffer to not get unbonded      This function will not work if operator has currently been selected for a job

unbondUtilityToken(address,address).details: A bonded operator selected for a job cannot unbond until they complete the job, or are slashed

params.recipient: address where to send the bonded tokens
